On 04 June 2025. Town, country: Washington, DC, US. Text: Trump issues ban on entry of nationals from 12 countries, including Afghanistan, Haiti and Iran, with partial restrictions on seven more nations. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: travel. Tag: immigration

On 03 May 2025. State, country: Jonglei, South Sudan. Text: Editor's note: A Twitter/X account claiming to represent the South Sudanese ethnic Nuer militant group Naath Defense Forces said that the government of South Sudan launched airstrikes on Nuer civilian areas in Old Fangak and nearby villages beginning early this morning. We have not yet seen reports surface in local media. We are monitoring for further information. - Theresa. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A

On 04 May 2025. State, country: North Kurdufan, Sudan. Text: Report: Air raid strikes el-Obeid, Sudan, according to Al Jazeera citing local sources. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A

On 23 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Sudan's warring military factions continue fighting in multiple parts of el-Fasher, Al-Arabiya reports. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 06 May 2025. State, country: Red Sea, Sudan. Text: Smoke seen rising, explosions heard at international airport in Port Sudan, Sudan, Al Jazeera, Al Arabiya report. Severity (from 1 to 4): 5. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: Al Arabiya
---
On 08 April 2025. State, country: Khartoum, Sudan. Text: Sudanese armed forces say have taken control of strategic sites west of Omdurman where RSF group was deployed. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 25 April 2025. State, country: River Nile, Sudan. Text: Editor's note: We are seeing reports of several people killed in a drone attack that targeted a camp for displaced people in Atbara in Sudan's River Nile State. The attack reportedly hit the city's power station, causing outages in both the Red Nile State and in the Red Sea State. We're monitoring for further clarification. - Theresa. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: power outages
---
On 20 May 2025. State, country: Khartoum, Sudan. Text: Report: Rapid Support Forces "target" University of Khartoum in Omdurman, Sudan, with explosive drones, sources tell Al Jazeera. Severity (from 1 to 4): 2. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: schools & universities
---
On 27 June 2025. State, country: Red Sea, Sudan. Text: Sudanese air defense stops drone attacks on Port Sudan following explosions heard near naval base, local media reports; no word yet from authorities. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 13 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Rebel group Sudan Liberation Movement calls on army for help in el-Fasher, Darfur, where paramilitary bombing continues, including in nearby displacement camps. Severity (from 1 to 4): 2. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: immigration

On 04 May 2025. State, country: Red Sea, Sudan. Text: Sudanese military, citing official, reports drone attack on Port Sudan targeted civilian facilities including air base and a cargo warehouse; unverified reports claim power outages in parts of city [corrects location struck]. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: power outages

On 26 April 2025. State, country: Khartoum, Sudan. Text: Egyptian media reports sounds of explosions in areas north of Omdurman, Sudan. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: explosions
---
On 08 May 2025. State, country: Red Sea, Sudan. Text: Sudanese Air Force College in Port Sudan struck during earlier drone barrage, Al Hadath reports. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: crime & courts. Tag: shootings
